text:
Mulyadi P. Tamsir (8 April 1981 – 9 January 2021) was an Indonesian student activist and politician. He was a member the People's Conscience Party. He was the chairman of the Muslim Students' Association from 2015 until 2018. Tamsir was born in Lampung, Indonesia.
Tamsir was killed in a plane crash on 9 January 2021 outside Jakarta near the Java Sea, aged 39.
